name: Panera Bread
description: Restaurants, Bakeries, Cafes, Bagels, Food, Soup, Salad, Sandwiches, Breakfast & Brunch

reviews.text: Good food, although quite bland. Good service. Always seems pricey given the portion sizes, however. Although that's my issue with Panera overall, nothing to do with this location.

I came here for lunch and was underwhelmed. They stopped using their panini toast. They use another toaster to heat their sandwiches now and they just don't taste the same. My soup was hot and fresh. The agave lemonade is sooo good, it's one of my favorite lemonades!
Rude counter help. Plenty of other places in the area to grab a quick meal on the run and not be served "attitude" on the side. Won't be back.

reviews.text: Great service! I love the tomato soup and grilled cheese. Such a fun place to have lunch after church. Definitely going to come back here.

We go a couple of times a month for dinner.  It is convenient and prices are good.  Breakfast all day is plus.  We have a family of 5 and there is something for everyone.  The cook will come out to make sure everything is OK and that is nice.   They seem to go through servers but the current server for evenings is great.  

Food is tasty.   They don't mind special orders.

I absolutely LOVE breakfast, but this place ruined it one weekend for my wife and I.  We tried it right after they opened.  My wife's eggs were runny and her other food was barely warm.  I ordered a "skillet," which I love at other breakfast spots.  What they brought me instead was a skillet-shaped ceramic dish.  The eggs were cold and runny, and all they did was take it back and reheat it - they didn't even re-fire the order.  Take a trip to Anna Marie's, the Limerick Diner or even Bob Evans - way better food, experience, and service - overall, more bang for your buck.

reviews.text: Still searching for tasty Chinese food in the Phoenixville area; tried delivery from Asian Cafe. The online ordering system worked nicely, though they don't accept Paypal (which I prefer for credit card security reasons) or Amex (which I prefer in general). They're a pan-Asia place, with Chinese, Japanese, and Thai dishes (this is not a good sign; it's like a diner with a menu that reads like a book -- how can you do that many things well? Answer: Likely you can't). I ordered both sashimi as well as a common Chinese dish (which I specified extra spicy). The sashimi was excellent! Very fresh and tasty. The Chinese dish had plenty of fresh vegetables, which is good. But it was  bland: not only didn't it have much flavor, but it also was lacking heat. Mind you, this was a dish listed with a pepper next to it on the menu, and I specified "extra spicy" in the order. And it was what I call "gloppy" -- typical Americanized Chinese food with a lot of oil. A good dish should have a thinner, tastier sauce. Also, I ordered the "large" portion, but it came with a rather small container of rice. And rather than putting the rice in a nice enviro-friendly  typical Chinese cardboard takeout box, the rice arrived in a Styrofoam container. My search for tasty Chinese food in Phoenixville shall continue. The nearest remains Margret Quo's Mandarin in Malvern / Frazer, though I doubt they deliver to Phoenixville (and you have to remember to ask for "no MSG.").

Some of the finest beef negamaki that I've ever had, anywhere!

Everything on the menu, from the bistro duck, to the Thai entrees and appetizers has been great so far except that the green tea ice cream was suffering from freezer burn. 

Check out the online-ordering option; it is one of the better ones I have seen on a restaurant website. Do eat in their dining room, since the staff is friendly and helpful, and you'll see those "punky punkin" walls for yourself!

(I wish they were closer to home.)

I really dig this restaurant!  Most of what I have had there is really good, only exception was their calamari.  I usually get the chicken satay!  It is REALLY good - yum!  They are always very friendly, they deliver, and food always seems fresh.

This place is a joke. After placing a phone in order, we arrived to a "restaurant" that was colder inside than outside (it was 23 degrees outside). Our order was incorrect - we only ordered 2 dishes - so we had to wait for them to cook the sweet 'n sour chicken we ordered. We got home with food that was super greasy & had a terrible taste. One of the fortune cookies was opened. I will NEVER be ordering from this dump again.
Food was actually OK, but there is no heat here. Do not think you are going to eat in.

reviews.text: The previous reviews had me worried so one day I took the chance and was actually surprise with how good the food was. I'll def come back

It's open pretty late.  11pm or later, even on weekdays.  So what?  You might ask.  It's just generic Chinese take-out with a bulletproof window.  There's a million of them.  Sure there are, but at 11:30pm, call or drive around and see if you can order from one.  Chances are they're closed.  That's what happened to me late one Sunday after working on cars all day at my friend's garage.  We thought it would be simple, those backlit yellow and red letter signs never go off.  The shining beacon in the urban night sky for wontons, dutchies, and chips.  Nope.

In fact, I had lived about two miles away when I first realized this.  So I made that two mile drive every time I wanted Chinese take-out in the final hours of the day.  One thing I should mention is that they do achieve wok hei, at least with the fried rice.  Wok hei, or "breath of the wok", is that sort of smokey burning flavor attained only from very high heat and the carbon steel of a wok.  Also I'm not sure if it was part of my conscious decision or sheer luck, because I now live less than a block away from China Star.  I can see it from my window as I write this.  It's 11:37pm on a Monday night, and yes, it's still open.

Average quality Chinese spot, but one of the only ones I've seen open the past few months. They have all the staples you'd want for a good price. Cash only, open late, combos on deck. Nothing was bad, but nothing amazing.

name: Mr Wish
description: Juice Bars & Smoothies, Food, Bubble Tea

reviews.text: Mr. Wish at Whitaker Avenue has such nice decorations and the workers are pretty nice. I bought five drinks on Tuesday, 11/5/19, and all the pearl milk tea tasted off. I thought it was just my drink but all my friends had weird drinks as well. I asked my other friends to try it and they said it wasn't just me and something was completely off. The boba in the pearl milk tea was not soft or even sweet, it tasted nothing like their signature tapioca. I contacted them through mrwishbencity about this. They opened my picture of the receipt and never replied. It's been four whole days and I'm really upset about this. Today, 11/9/19, I bought the tiger shark and it's nothing as advertised. My friend who works at the Chinatown Mr. Wish said this is nothing like the tiger shark. When she drank it, she said it tastes like regular milk and the boba is so hard. It's as if they didn't make the boba the way they were supposed to make it.

Mr. Wish at Whitaker Avenue has such nice decorations and the workers are pretty nice. I bought five drinks on Tuesday, 11/5/19, and all the pearl milk tea tasted off. I thought it was just my drink but we all had weird drinks. I asked my other friends to try it and they said something was completely off. The boba in the pearl milk tea was not soft or even sweet, it tasted nothing like their signature tapioca. I contacted them through mrwishbencity about this. They opened my picture of receipt and never replied. It's been two whole days and I'm really upset about this. I would've given it a one if it wasn't for their good service.

This is my go-to bubble tea location! I love their selection of drinks, which includes everything from milk tea to smoothies and sherbets. Although they've only recently opened, this establishment is inviting. Their employees are kind and are always prompt in greeting customers. 

My favorites here are the 3Q Milk Tea and the Avocado Smoothie. Definitely check this place out!

name: China Wok
description: Specialty Food, Chinese, Ethnic Food, Restaurants, Food

reviews.text: You get the most bang for your buck at China Wok. Every other asian restaurant charges $2-3 more on a lot of dishes than what China Wok charges such as a popular favorite General Tso's, dumplings, and lo meins. Plus China Wok delivers and it is a better fit for customers that want to pick up their chinese. China Wok was also the first chinese take out restaurant to be established in Swedesboro and Logan Township. I've had the best shrimp rolls, general, house fried rice, sweet sour chicken, and fried dumplings from this place. The only down side is it is not a fancy sit down chinese restaurant like tokyo nor do they sell sushi.

This isn't Chinatown, but for your local Chinese food fix China Wok is just fine.
Fast delivery and courteous service.
The food is better than average at a good price.
They don't do fancy food, for that there's other places in the area, but if your a pork fried rice, egg roll, Spare rib etc. type of person this place is fine. 5 stars for the fast delivery.

DIRTY! Ordered from here simply for delivery. First time ordering from here. 30 dollars worth of food just to find a bug in my chicken and broccoli. Totally disgusting and won't be ordering from here ever again.

name: Jeni's Splendid Ice Creams
description: Desserts, Ice Cream & Frozen Yogurt, Food

reviews.text:
I don't know what the big deal is about this brand. Maybe you have to 'be there' as an Elite Yelper in the newest store to get the full experience. I dunno, but somehow I doubt it. 

Nothing wrong with this location just as there's nothing inherently WRONG with this ice cream, but none of the flavors I tried made me want to keep buying it. The first one I ever tried was the Brambleberry Crisp. Did not even finish the pint. The 'crisp' part was annoying to eat, very hard in comparison to the other ingredients and I did not find the fruit swirl to be especially tasty.

The Darkest Chocolate, which I bought at Whole Foods, was fine but I will continue buying Haagen Dazs chocolate over this. I think it tastes better.

Pistachio Macaron, also purchased at Whole Foods, was too sweet and there was a dearth of pistachios. Again, I'll take Haagen Daz Pistachio over this, as it is absolutely loaded with large pistachio pieces, the flavor base is mild and it doesn't put me into a sugar coma. Talenti Pistachio gelato is a second runner up to Haagen Daz's for a full nut experience.

Sure, it's nice that Jeni Bauer has been around since the late 1990, started out small and is now nationwide. Kudos to an enterprising, hard working woman. Even though I don't eat ice cream very often, $12 a pint is an extravagance for me, especially as none of the flavors appeal in the least.

Taste is highly subjective and clearly Ms. Bauer has an enormous fan base that doesn't include me.

My, oh my. For a while, I thought this place was only in Chicago. I've been here a couple of times and never really looked into other locations. Thankfully, my stupidity was mitigated by Jeni's explosive expansion into the Philadelphia region with two locations - Fishtown and Center City. I decided to make the trip with some friends from across town to get to Fishtown and try the ice cream I so longed for. Filled with unique flavors, each type had the rich, deliciousness all dairy ice cream SHOULD have. For every minute that passed, my mouth was watering at the idea of being in one of the greatest places to exist on this earth.

When I got there, it was the same, simple design that greets you with a warm feeling of "hey, you're home now. Jeni's is here for you". I quickly got my favorites - Gooey Butter cake, Blueberry Crisp, and Honey Vanilla bean. When put together, they make an ultimate combo that slaps ur tastebuds yelling "what have you been doing eating those nasty tubs of ice cream from Acme?" As soon as I sat down with the waffle pieces and the scoops of ice cream, I dived into the winter wonderland. Even the thought of the taste salivates my mind, and this ice cream is hard to beat in its consistency anywhere else. But within minutes, the three scoops were gone. Then I remembered, this place has kinda mid portions for the price - no wonder I bought those tubs of Ben and Jerrys.

Despite the portions, this magical place gives you a surreal experience of ice cream flavors that will hopefully finish off the hefty meal you grab or satisfy that sweet tooth that came in with.

Decent ice cream, it's good for sure, but honestly not anything wildly different than other local ice cream shops. Nice store design with frontage of Frankford Ave, we appreciate the modern design in the neighborhood. 2 stars though because the price is outrageous. I purchased two kids sized cups. To be clear, that is literally two child sized small scoops, two scoops total! Not a couple scoops or a full bowl.  Total $10. Wow. Like really?  We love to support local business here in the neighborhood, and regularly spend a premium to do so and have for years.  Jeni's is however NOT a true local business. They have national distribution and locations all over the US, so it feels somehow off to have a national company charging those kind of prices when Igloo and Weckerlys are equally as good, arguably better (that's subjective) with better price points for what you get. Van Leeuwans soon to follow curious where they will stand.  With national scale and distribution, price points can and should theoretically be held artificially lower. Anyway, enjoy either way. Welcome to Fishtown.

name: Panera Bread
description: American (New), Restaurants, Bakeries, Food, Sandwiches, Soup, Salad, Bagels, Breakfast & Brunch

reviews.text:
We stopped at this Panera on the way home. It was an enjoyable experience from placing the order til eating it.  The store is clean and well stocked.  The cashier was polite and welcoming. 
The Baja bowl was delicious. It had a nice mix of ingredients. My daughter was pleased that a healthy  Keto meal was available. My other daughter had the chicken salad sandwich with chicken noodle soup. (Can you tell she likes  chicken) Both the Sammie 
and soup were tasty! I had 1/2 Fuji Apple salad and vegetable soup. The soup was filled with veggies and perfect for a cold day. The salad was good. I didn't realize it came with chicken I actually wanted more greens. I went back to the server. She was so nice and apologetic even though it wasn't her fault. She happily gave me more greens. 
The tea here is Republic of Tea brand so it's good. My daughters were happy with their coffee drinks.

Wonderful service! Ordered delivery, and my special requests and order was followed to a T. Went above and beyond too. Everything is fresh, packaged carefully, and tastes great. 

Thank you! My prior delivery experiences have been great as well. Consistent, and during this pandemic, they deserve extra credit. 5 stars for sure! 

P.S. I recommend trying their strawberry lemonade and pastries, if you haven't yet! Bagels are always great too.

In the spring of 2011 I worked near this location.  Every Wednesday a co-worker would pick up the lunches for us.  The food was fairly decent which is why this is a 2 star as opposed to a 1 star review.  My issue is that the business REFUSES to post pricing on their menus.  I just looked @ Panera's website and there is STILL no prices whatever on their menus.  People are on fixed budgets and have fixed means of income for crying out loud?!  I would therefore be @ the mercy of the honesty of the then co-worker as to how much I would be charged - thankfully said person is honest.  If I remember correctly when she called in the orders she was not apprised of the prices until she went over to pick up the stuff - she's much more comfortable about driving on Street Road than I am or I'd go over to check it out myself.  I am surprised no one mentioned this as you would think there would be local or state legislation requiring pricing be placed on menus - printed or online.  This BTW is the ONLY food business I ever encountered this with.  Even today (1/23/17) there is NO pricing on their online menu; they tout having a transparent menu - without pricing as far as I'm concerned it is NOT transparent enough!  I neither live nor work near one of their locations currently and with NO pricing posted I definitely will not go out of my way to patronize these locations.

reviews.text: Been here a few times since moving in to Elsmere. I've found the staff super friendly and nice. Every time I've gone in the offerings are fresh and they've always had what I wanted.

i go here 3-4 times a week as it is around the corner from work but no more. the staff are rude and the owner is the worst. the old lady that is their every day was compaling that he was not in and she was all by her self and i can see where is was coming from as 12 people were in line and it took over 20 minutes to order my sub. the owner did arrive finally when i was second in line and he actually took my order. he asked me what do you want (extreamly rude but this is not the worst) which i replied a FT long honey oat with buffalo chicken he then asks what bread i once again say honey oat foot long and then he says ok ft long what type of bread do you want? i said this is the third time i have told you honey oat. he got the picture YAY! he put the cheese on and toasted the sub. he then said what else do you want (i am shocked by the rudeness) but i just don't say anything except lettuce tomato cucumber so he puts the lettuce and cucumbers on and forgets the tomato. i have just about had enough so i said stop slow down(he was rushing and not paying attention to what is going on and the lady told him I said tomato and she was making some one elses sub) and listen to what i am saying because i should not have to keep repeating my self. his reply is so do you want this sub? i said yes i do and i do not appreciate the attitude because i have been waiting over 20 minutes because you were late to work. his reply was do not speak to me like that and i just lost it. i did not swear at him i just explained how unprofessional he is being and the fact his consists of making a sub and he does not have the capacity to do so. he then asks again do want the sub i reply yes of course i need to eat lunch sometime today. he then throws my sub in the bin and says get out. during this 4 or 5 people walked out because of his attitude. its fair to say i will not be going back ever again! STAY AWAY!

I'm severely handicapped & took a recent trip to this Subway to order a sub. There was a sign on the front door that said to use the side door. There is no side door. There is only a front door & a back door. To get to the back door, you must either walk through the grass to the right, or walk in the middle of the road, because there is no sidewalk on the side of Subway, along with the non existent side door. I could see a few customers inside, & the lady employee, & I tried waving at them to get someone to open the front door, as I cannot open doors without assistance, & everyone inside either laughed & shook  their heads, or pretended not to hear me. Some junkie finally opened the door & the laughing customers kept laughing & making comments. I asked if my being handicapped amuses them & they said it's hilarious because I was causing a scene. I wasn't originally causing a scene. I explained that there's no side door & I'm not struggling to get stuck in the grass or in middle of the road & get hit by a car. Employee was also laughing her @$$ off & I said to let me out. Door was locked & she laughed & said she was too busy to let me out. 
Her excuse for the front door being locked was because she's working alone & doesn't want to get robbed. Nobody can park out front, only in back, so, if she was going to get robbed, getaway car would be out back. There's nowhere for a robber to run away out front, except right into the 5 way intersection directly out front. Horrible things were said to me by the customers (ask me)
I'm never going back there. She can go rot like Jared!

reviews.text: Won't be going back.  I orderer ONE cheesesteak and it was the worst cheesesteak I've ever had.  How can you mess up a cheesesteak?  There was very little meat on the roll.  The meat that was there was black from being on the grill for too long and the chesse - non exsistant.

This is really great pizza. The Hawaiian pizza has fresh pineapple not from a can. They will make pizza slices with what you want, but they don't really want to. Compared to what is in the area, this one is the best pizza.

Just moved the the neighborhood a few months ago and Pizza Land is now my family's go to pizza spot.  I call my order in and it's usually ready within a half an hour.  They use great ingredients for toppings.  Olives are real, not the cheap sliced ones you get in a can.  Staff is cordial even while busy with orders.

reviews.text:
My first love, my only love.


When I tell you I was happy when they re-opened, I screamed cried. I cried over water ice. They're that good.

I've been coming here since I was a little kid. We use to spend all our money, before parents started giving their kids $40 a day, on water ice and hugs. I'm pretty sure I never ate real food. Just this water ice. That's how good it is.

Roadmap to Success in life:

Sunday Morning
1. Wake Up.
2. Eat breakfast.
3. GO TO ITALIANOS AND GET WATER ICE AT 10:00 A.M. BECAUSE IT'S SO SCRUMPTIOUS AND WILL PUT YOU IN A GOOD MOOD FOR AT LEAST THE NEXT 12 HOURS. 

Gelati: 
If you want to keep it real-ish and feel like you're doing your body good, get mango water ice and vanilla ice cream. This treat is justifiable: The mango water ice actually tastes like mangoes, not overly concentrated mango syrup typically paired with sticky rice found at greasy chopsticks joints.

If you want to indulge your sophisticated side, try vanilla water ice with coffee ice cream. It tastes much better than any of that frappuccino shit you get at _______. This concoction tastes like somebody smashed together equal parts sugar and vanilla and dumped it over frozen creamy coffee. You'll feel mature eating it, but you'll probably get brain freeze. Irony. Enjoy it.

 Plain Water Ice:
Amaretto. It's pretty amazing that amaretto water ice tastes like amaretto cream without any actual cream in the water...ice. I bet this is like whatever Alice came across in Wonderland that kept making her DRINK ME even after growing and shrinking. It's that good. Promise.
Best in south philly , only bad thing is they open late and close early .  Staff is always great . Old man waters down the outside keeps it clean .  Great place

reviews.text:
I'm not surprised that Goodburger closed down. Especially with such competitors as 5 Guys or one of the many gastropubs that offer some very tasty burgers.

Goodburger was just A-OK by my standards. But I won't go crying over it anytime soon...

I ate at Good Burger the other night because I got to the city later than I wanted too and it was faster than eating at someplace like Alma De Cuba or Rouge which is where I wanted to eat (Rouge was so packed it looked like it had people falling out of the place literally).  So Mike was like lets just eat at Good Burger, they have a pretty good burger.
So we did.  And it was Good.  Seriously though, the service is out of this world frustrating.  I don't mind if people can't speak English in this country...so long as I don't have to deal with talking to them in a situation where they need to be talking to people as 80% of their job.  I tried ordering a 5.5 Burger with The Works (sans Tomato), and she said that it came to 9.00 or whatever.  But the register said double that amount and I kept trying to tell her I wasn't ordering two of them.  But she couldn't comprehend.  So eventually the girl next to her took over the register and expedited the process.  
Anyways I got my food about ten minutes later, which is 5 minutes less than my friends took...and he ordered the same thing as me...and he ordered before me.  What a world we live in.
So the Burger itself was pretty darn perfect.  Juicy, full of toppings, but the meat stood out and wasn't overwhelmed by them.  The fries were also a delicious surprise and they came with some of that dipping sauce that seems to be all the rage now in Philly everywhere you go that serves Pommes Frittes.  Was it better than Five Guys?  It was probably a little less greasy, but all in all a similar taste and quality I would say.  I'd definitely go again if the mood should strike me for a reasonably priced Burger that will take a few minutes longer than McDonalds...and Rouge is packed because its the first day the weather is nice in weeks and people come to the city en masse.  Who can blame them though?

I was disappointed from the start when the cashier did not great me with "Welcome to Good Burger, home of the good burger can I take your order?" If you  are going to rip off a tv show skit/movie do it right! Also looking at the menu and seeing I was going to pay 6+ dollars for just a burger didn't sit to well with my broke ass self. I had to try it though so I ordered my burger well done and it was done in a few minutes. The burger was pretty tasty and had a little kick which I liked but nothing overwhelmingly spectacular. The music was turned down to a low murr so I hummed along with the pop music that I am embarrassed to know the words to. 
I will still stick with Five Guys when I am in the mood for a chest tightening burger.

reviews.text: This Subway beats every subway I have ever been to. All of their food is fresh and their staff is extremely friendly. When not knowing what to order the staff makes excellent recommendations. Inside, it is very clean and behind the counter is clean and organized; everything a customer would like to see at a restaurant. Will always pick this subway over any other.

Live up by Grand View and pass not 1 but 2 locations. And there a reason. This location cares and has never made a mistake before. Sure I waited a few times but you know what I don't care. The food was fresh and delicious. Recommend the steak sandwich. Or the meatballs I can't judge in the lunch meat.. pregnancy prevents that. But I'm sure it's delicious to. Will update in April 2022 and let you fellow yelpers know.
This your normal subway, nothing special about it. Some of the staff can be rude. If you go early morning it seems to be better then when I go later in the day.

name: Touch of Class
description: Specialty Food, Candy Stores, Food, Shopping

reviews.text:
I am constantly on the lookout for a good gift basket retailer since one of my unofficial jobs at my company is to send bday/wedding/congrats/goodbye/new baby/you-name-it gifts. When I was tasked with sending 40+ last-minute quality baskets to our guests in a foreign (to me) city, I was SO happy to find Touch of Class. However, as good as the website looked, I was a little hesitant to believe the hype only because I have been let down before. Everything about this place blew my mind. The snacks are not only things that you would actually want to eat, most of them are roasted BY the owners! Renee (co-owner) sat on the phone with me while I hand-picked the items for our baskets and gave me her biased, yet well versed opinions. I actually had fun "designing" these baskets with her when normally I absolutely loathe the process of sorting through crappy unappetizing snacks.
When I went to pick the baskets up from the store, I was totally blown away by the selection of treats available in-store. They have any kind of nut, chocolate, fruit, snack combo imaginable. After sampling I also found them to be quality and delicious, not an easy feat. The presentation of the baskets was beautiful - I could see that the staff really put time into making them, bows and all. I didn't mention that I gave them less than 3 days to design, stock and assemble.. and they were completed with a smile (and a hug!). The prices were what I asked without sacraficing the content.
I will definitely return to Touch of Class and have already recommended them to a friend. You cannot go wrong with this place!

Had to grab a last minute hostess gift. Of course Touch of class never disappoints and had me on my way in no time. Whether I have an hour to kill looking around or need a gift in a hurry they couldn't be more helpful. 
Thanks Touch of Class!

The last review is dated and I'm glad I found this place. Was waiting for pizza next store and went inside to look around. Found GREAT gifts for graduation and Mother's Day. Lots of items to be monogrammed and candy and snacks for every taste.

reviews.text:
Most Subways are just that Subways .... but the Subway in Perkasie was one of the original few in the area for a long time. The Owner, Nick, is a great guy who really cares about the patrons who are customers at his business. Unlike other chains (and other Subways for that matter) where there seems to be constant turnover of employees. The same few Sandwich "Artists" have been there from almost the beginning. This is refreshing and it's like seeing old friends when you walk into places that are able to retain their valuable employees. 

Subway seems to be trying to stay current with their customer base in the heavy promotion of the $5 sub deal. They have also added flatbeards, apples, etc as more health conscience alternatives to the traditional sandwich. And even though they did away with the stamps and cards for a free 6" sandwich every 9th time -- they now offer an electronic card that accumulates points that are good towards free sandwiches, drinks, cookies, etc. 

You know what you are going to get walking into subway but the franchise in Perkasie is different and that is due to its employees ....  and that's the bottom line.

Great place to grab a sandwich for lunch. The man working behind the counter had excellent customer service, and was very personable. He added a friendly personality to what is more or less a quick in and out sandwich shop. Would recommend for an affordable, healthier, quick lunch or dinner option.

Great service, always friendly and will help you with anything. Their food there is good, they keep their working area clean and well covered. Every time we come in here, we see the same guy, I'm not sure what his name is, but on a Friday night he is always there, working alone. He is great, great attitude and friendly. He is really fast and keeps the line going.
 They have a rewards card you can get here also so if you have enough points, you can get some sandwiches free. Great place to eat when you don't really feel like waiting at a table in a restaurant and just want to go home and get filled up or eat real quick here.

reviews.text: Best Chinese food in the area. Their rice is not leaded with grease, they provide a vegetarian menu and affordable.  You can pay with card get the  phone or order on their website  when the oder is over $20 you get free crab ragoons. Their scallion pancakes are delicious.

I used to get deliveries from this place, but saw info and pics online about the disgusting ways they prepare food outside behind the restaurant.  Vegetables on the ground thrown into a cooking pot for example...so filthy.  They need to be reported, better yet:  Shut 'em down!!

When I order from them they always deliver pretty quickly and sometimes includes a free item. I've had their won ton soup, dumplings and a few of their platters by now and they don't disappoint. One time I tried to say what time I wanted them to come by and they arrived a half hour sooner but other than that always a good experience.

reviews.text: They haven't really been doing so good when it comes to social distancing. I have been there when there wasn't a pandemic and I enjoyed them much more
Suppose to close at 8- walked in at 7:45 and they said they were closed!! Don't post your hours til 8 and close earlier than that time

Friendly employees, who now after making my sandwich a gazillion times, greet me with a very warm welcome and know exactly what I want.

My usual is a foot long chicken breast sandwich on honey oat bread. I have the bread scooped out and the chicken breast toasted. They used to keep the chicken in a warmer, but that recently changed and they now keep it with the cold meats. I also get lettuce, tomato, spinach and cucumbers with salt & pepper and ranch dressing. It always hits the spot!

Just recently I switched it up and ordered the chicken on honey oat but with spinach, tomatoes, hot peppers, pickles, salt & pepper with chipotle sauce.

They also have soups. My personal favorite is the brown rice with chicken.

Don't forget a point card. For every $1 you spend, you get a point and it adds up pretty quickly. I get a free foot long sandwich at least once a month, just by hitting $75 points.

reviews.text: Always good fast service. Everything is kept clean and the staff is always friendly definitely one of the better Subways around.

When the owners are there this is a great spot to grab a quick meal but when their one female employee is working service is awful! She is rude, 2nd time I've had the experience with her. Supposed to be open at 9am I arrived at 9:30 and was told I had to wait because she wasn't ready. Had an attitude like I was bothering her by giving her my business.  Won't go back!

Nice quiet place at 8pm and the owner had a clean establishment. The kids ordered their simple sandwiches and I ordered my wrap and my husband ordered a chopped salad. The gentleman was very polite and accurate. A little disoriented but I think we may have caught him at closing time. But it was clean and ready.

description: Juice Bars & Smoothies, Food, Bubble Tea, Coffee & Tea

reviews.text: Yesterday i came there to order the yogurt green tea. It was terrible, i made me stomachade.

The restaurant is very clean and decently big! There is adequate seating for all party sizes. The staff is attentive and helpful with your order. The bubble tea options are very large and very customizable. The tea itself is delicious and good quality. The most noteworthy thing about Kung Fu Tea is the bubbles. You can go to a million bubble tea locations as many times as you choose and consistently receive boba that is not quite right, or constantly different in quality. But this is not an issue at Kung Fu Tea. The bubbles are always perfectly made and consistently made. No matter when you go or how often you frequent the place, you can count on receiving perfectly cooked, delicious boba in your bubble tea. If chains turn you off to trying this bubble tea, I can assure you that quality is not affected by that factor. It is really worth a try!
Kung Fu tea staff rude. Tea overpriced and not good. They say they take credit cards but won't take them under $10.00.

reviews.text: stopped here for a quick lunch.  they have their own seating section which is nice so you don't have to fight for a table in the middle of the mall.  Had the sesame chicken with lo mein.  both pretty good.   also had an order of dumplings. they were pretty good too.  not as doughy as some chinese restaurants but better than most japanese restaurants i have had.  would eat here again if looking for a quick lunch in the mall.
Great place to grab quick bite. Make sure you try the egg rolls, not filling but very tasty.

Convenient mall Chinese food--but how does it taste? A lot of you young 'uns may not remember this, but back in the 1980s women's magazines in America would have these startlingly inauthentic "Chinese" recipes. You'd see recipes like "Chinese pineapple surprise" which was boneless chicken, pineapple, ketchup, and just a hint of soy sauce for that "unique Asian flavor." 

I remember my mom cooking those sorts of things. And the food at this place tastes just like that! You don't taste garlic or rice wine or pepper or sesame oil. Just plain ol' chicken and soy sauce and rice. It's not terrible but definitely not worth a detour. Cheap as heck, though: my two-entree meal was like $7. (See pic.) Fellow Gen X and older folks, relive the American Chinese food of the 70s and 80s right here in sunny Delaware!

description: Restaurants, Food, Juice Bars & Smoothies, Sushi Bars

reviews.text: For a sushi stand in the middle of the mall, this place is exceptional. Good sushi, friendly staff, and did I mention good fish?!  I would choose this sushi bar over many restaurants. The menu is a little misleading so confirm what you want with the staff.

The only reason I did 4 and not 5 is the weird pricing. Sometimes it's $9.95 and sometimes it's $10.30, but I usually always order the same thing. It's amazing though. I was a little wary at first because I thought it'd be an express kind of thing (low quality, get in get out kinda deal). Pleasantly surprised though!!! Amazing quality, very polite, and it's not super expensive! I've eaten here about 10 times already and never once was I disappointed.

I was pleasantly surprised at the quality of food considering its a little stand located on the first floor of the plymouth meeting mall.  Due to the lack of traffic in this mall, you shouldn't have to wait long.  There is a wraparound bar (minus alcohol) for you to sit and eat.

Clean, fast, courteous. 

I tried the fruit smoothie assuming it was fresh fruit and ice..it is not! Still was ok..tried the green apple but not what I expected. 

They have numerous rolls,standard and special, and plenty of beverages to choose from including bubble tea 

The Philadelphia roll was fresh and so yummy,  looking forward to trying the miso soup

reviews.text: Eat Lunch here occasionally and its very good. I get the 6 inch oven roasted chicken sandwich with bacon, cheddar cheese, lettuce, and bbq sauce every time and it is tasty. For a little extra you can make it a combo and add chips and a fountain drink. I like having lunch here because you don't leave with that glutenous feeling after having a sandwich unlike at some other places. Services is great and after coming here a few times one of the employees even remembered me and my co-workers orders.

I have been eating at Subway since I was a little I have always loved it until today I had the nastiest customer service I have ever seen. I myself have worked in the food industry and I know it is all about the customer, I felt the complete opposite. When I walked into the store there was no one at the counter and when she came she said nothing to me but looked at me, I just thought well maybe she is having a bad day and continued to tell her my order. I told her "light oil" and instead she put started to put mayo I told her "No i'm sorry I said oil." I absolutely hate mayo and she tried to argue with me and said "You said light mayo" she then took her glove inside out and started to wipe the mayo off of my sandwich it had to be the most unsanitary thing I have ever seen. I grabbed a bag of chips and put them on the counter she rang me up without asking did I want the which I did want the one with the sandwich, chips and drink she then rolled her eyes and just told me the total. I had to grab my own fountain cup and than there were no straws! I asked her for a straw and her response was her shaking her head! I was furious but I only had a 30 min lunch break, I have never been treated so rudely by someone before.

The only Subway on the main line! The staff is well informed, but they usually tend to be college students. They made me an awesome Autumn Turkey Sandwich that was topped off with their new cranberry sauce. The location can be crowded due to it's location, but the line moves quick. It has a small TV, but the staff always knows what to play. They recently added new sliding glass over the condiments so you can easily interact with staff.

Start with a crunchy base of lettuce, spinach, American cheese, tomatoes, cucumbers, green peppers, black olives and red onions, then add juicy shaved steak and top with the NEW Sweet Onion Teriyaki sauce that finishes it all up with notes of sesame, garlic and black pepper.

It starts with crunchy veggies—lettuce, spinach, tomatoes, cucumbers, green peppers, black olives, and red onions followed by our juicy, grilled chicken strips that are topped with our delicious NEW Sweet Onion Teriyaki Sauce. It’s one sweet and tangy tasting salad.

name: Popeyes Louisiana Kitchen
description: American (Traditional), Fast Food, Chicken Wings, Restaurants

reviews.text:
Even for a Popeye's, this place is pretty bad.  Its not filthy, but it's definitely not clean.  The food is below average for a Popeye's and the service is friendly on the surface though has its edges (more on that in a moment).  
I don't expect white glove clean at any fast food joint, but this one made me feel like I was at Market East Station rather than in the suburbs.  The only available table has the crumb and grease remnants of former occupants and the seat had a black gummy substance on it which has yet to be identified.
I ordered chicken nuggets, a mistake I realized almost immediately.  The one or two times a year I get Popeye's, I should stick with the fried chicken or the chicken fingers at a minimum.  At least with the fingers, you get some of that vascular traffic jamming crunchy action.  So half the nuggets were actually pretty good, with the crunchy batter.  The other half seemed breaded and microwaved.  They held their heat like microwaved nuggets and were much mushier than the other half of the batch.  I'm guessing they had about five ready when I asked for a 9 piece so they then micro'd the balance.  Just a guess but there was a distinct difference .  On the window of this "restaurant" was a sign that said "try our signature dipping sauces!"  So when my food came up, they guy didn't even ask me if I wanted any sauce.  I asked for some and instead of asking me which one I'd like, he chose one (Spicy and Sweet or something like that) and said "this is the best one".  Well, I quickly discovered that he and I have very different tastes and went back to get something I might actually enjoy.  I asked for the Mardi Gras mustard and he was visibly annoyed.  Whether he was annoyed that I was costing him an extra sauce or that I disagreed with him was not clear.  But he didn't like my request and didn't care if I knew it.  Worse is that he appeared to be the owner and manager.  Bad example.  The Mardi Gras mustard was ok (heavy horseradish).  The food was just boring considering it will cost me an hour off the end of my life.  The biscuit was a hockey puck.  Total BS.  You can't even get that right?
I've already spent more time than I planned on a review of a fast food place but I also want to note that the door was broken and kept flying wide open.  Since it was very cold outside, this was a problem.  I got up to close it once but refused to do it twice.  I ate fast and left.  I probably won't be back.  Not even once a year.

(3.5) ~ good overall food & service.  MY WISH:  That they'd add Popeye's Sweet Potato Pies to their menu;-)

OUR MENU:
** Strawberry Fanta Soda = (4) very good
** Biscuits = (4) very good...like these better than KFC;-)
* Chicken(mild) = (3.5) good
* Chicken(spicy) = (3.5) good
* MudPie = (3.5) good

I buy chicken from here regularly.  The customer service is very nice, the chicken is always well-cooked and tasty.  The place looks clean.  The only problem is that sometimes they're sold out of certain things, and if it's after work and I"m in a hurry, I just don't have time to wait for it to cook.  Other than that, I love this place - good people working there, always nice & friendly.

name: BAMBU
description: Desserts, Bubble Tea, Juice Bars & Smoothies, Food, Coffee & Tea, Restaurants, Vietnamese

reviews.text: Let's just say this place adds sweetening syrup to their sugar cane juice .. that's crazy!!! We ordered two pressed sugar cane juice with ice and one with no ice. My mom happened to saw the staff add the syrup into the last juice (no ice) before sealing it. When we received our order we told the cashier that we don't want ours with added sugar, she went behind the curtain to ask, came back and told us sugar wasn't added into the juices. I then stated that "my mother saw" it. The nice cashier went back in again to confirm the story. Another female staff (the one who made our drinks) came out and claimed that sugar was only added to the order with no ice (which doesn't make sense one bit). She took back the drink with no ice and made us a new order. Sorry for the rant, but lesson to take away is always ask beforehand when ordering sugar cane juice anywhere.

This place is a must try! You have to go to Bambu and try their Vietnamese Che(dessert), especially number 1-3 you don't know what you've been missing out if you haven't. I drink bubble tea and go to all sorts of dessert places but this is more like bubble tea to the max. They give you so much great stuff in their che from taro, tapiocas, jellies, and coconut and more. Also their teas are great, I would recommend the jasmine or Thai or even be more adventurous and try Vietnamese and tropical flavors. Been here like a dozen times and will keep on coming as long as they keep on serving. Would love for them to expand into center city and beyond.
Love it here!! Easily becoming my next obsession!! My favorites are the desserts(che) which are like coconut parfaits!

reviews.text:
Lunch today tuna on wheat flatbread spinach, cheese sweet onion sauce black olives and jalapeños. All crafted by a very service oriented friendly CK. Great post workout meal! Restaurant is clean restroom clean stocked and pleasant sunny dining room and great music! Thanks CK for making us feel special!
Location is conveniently accessed and has plenty of parking in a safe lot.

Best Subway in the area. Better quality and always fresher veggies then the other ones I have been to. Staff is great, and friendly. I order in the app and it's always ready before I get there. I come here often and they always get the order right. I recommend everyone to try this location.

I came in to the Subway that I used to frequent for lunch on Tuesday, Aug 20, 12:38 pm. The restaurant was clean, and the food neatly on display appeared fresh. The store had just a couple of customers, and that was surprising being it was during the height of lunch hour. The gentleman behind the counter greeted me with, Hello, it's been a long time. He was the owner he had introduced himself years ago when I was a regular customer. I ordered my food a Spicy Italian on Herbs and Cheese roll and had requested my sauce be placed on the bread. There were some new toppings, so I was checking them out and not paying attention to the construction of my sub. The man asked sauce on top; I replied with "Did you put a good bit on the roll," I order it on the roll to help prevent it from dripping on my clothes. He made an angry face and proceeded to lift the contents off the roll and show me, I asked if there was a problem and he went on to reprimand me for having asked for a little on the bread, I may have used the word little but was only wanting to know if he put any on the bread because I wasn't paying attention and so that I knew there was sauce on it. There was no one in line behind me, yet so I was taken back by his giving me attitude. I took my sub to go, it was good but I have always been respectful to this guy and even tolerated his bad talking Subway corporation in the past because "they don't support the owners just have demands on them" I had given him frequent receipt reviews all positive and even did a yelp review years ago that was also very positive. A woman was at the register and was very kind, thanking me for coming in. When I exited the store, it was the last time I will ever go there. Maybe this explains how on a summer day during the lunch rush near a theme park, the store was not busy? After posting my briefly of displeasure with on the receipt survey I received an email from the owner, it was a boilerplate message saying he shared my feedback with his team to improve customer service. That was even more of an insult and showed how much he doesn't care about his customers. When I exited the store, it was the last time I would be there.​

reviews.text: I will probably never order from here again. They do have a large variety of options on their menu and the taste is good BUT I've ordered here 3 times and the experience was not the best on every occasion. The last experience I had was the one that caused me not to go back. I sat at the counter and discussed my order with owner. She told me that she took my order and 15 minutes later I found out that she never actually took my order so I walked back to work and called the same order in. I had to go back several times on that same order just to get it correct. They were apologetic BUT I still will never come back. They have reasonable hours and again the menu is large, but you'll have to go into the actual store to see the entire menu.

Decided to try this place after passing it on Main Street a few times. It's our breakfast spot now. Everything we've ordered has come out amazing and delicious. If there's an issue it's corrected immediately. They definitely know how to do breakfast!

I went in and immediately felt that old school diner vibe.  The waitress was pretty cool. Definitely a place that locals frequent, so you know the good is mmmm mmmm good. I ordered the loaded home fries , but I tweaked them a bit. Superb! I'm definitely coming back sooner rather than later! Nice people & delicious food, win-win.

reviews.text: This is the best subway I've ever been to. The best food and so clean. I'll never eat at another subway!

went to this location for the first time and sad to say they dont stand up to the standards of other subways i went to before.

 i ordered tuna hoagie witj extra lettuce and cheese and it was disappointing. they put a little tuna on the roll and the extra lettuce i asked for was like 10 little shreds of lettuce. there was nothing to this sandwich besides bread.

 i would not come back here ever waste of money. 

the staff were angry and looked like they didnt want to serve customers and the vibe of the place was terrible. i wont be returning.

Boyyy..let me tell you...still sitting in there as I write this review..the south-asian man serving me refused to remind me of what a BMT was? He said he didnt remember...then when i pressed a little more, he decided to get me out of his face quicker by telling me.
Never asked me if i wanted it toasted...but said "What else? (on the sandwich)" i had to ask that he not continue to veggies but toast.
Snatched my card etc.
Listen..rule of thumb...meanness is an illness, you should have called out of work.

3 stars because the lady who was there, i heard how she interacted with other customers and she was polite

reviews.text: If you want a ton of food for 10 bucks, this is the place to go to. The food is hearty and greasy. Great value and I love their spring rolls.

Given the options in the area for chinese fast food, this place is pretty good. Their sauteed string beans are hit or miss depending on the time of season or more specifically the freshness of the beans they have to work with. Their lo mein noodles are just okay. Their rice is kind of dry and tasteless. Their orange chicken is pretty good and consistent.

This place is perfect for no-frills Chinese food. Nothing super creative but also not a letdown.  Hot and sour soup is decent and they'll make you a combo with pretty much anything if you ask.  

As stated in another review, this place is strictly takeout.

reviews.text: We love Angelos ... one issue though ... the last time they delivered.. the driver told us to use delivery dude next time ... ok whatever .. so I did ... and they charge there fees .. $5 Ok normal tax and what not ... then $7 delivery fee (what the ??? ) then they expect a tip ... (I'm find throwing the driver 20% not ok with being raked threw the coals with a $ 7 delivery fee on top of everything most places at 2.99 ... )unfortunately  because of this they are losing business by not just me ... smh it's sad too because it's the only decent place in kop

I called Angelo's and was told I had to order online for delivery.  The online system is not user friendly at all and did not have all of the choices available.  I called back.  The person I spoke with was very helpful and friendly.  He explained to me how to enter online for a white pizza, but that I still needed to order through the online system.  He even called me back to verify what I wanted once he received the online order.  The pizza was actually delivered 5 minutes before the time requested, so I was happy about that.  But the pizza was delivered room temperature.  A co-worker told me that they used here once before and it was not hot when delivered, but I tried it one more time.  There is not a lot of delivery choices in KoP.  But I will not be going back unless I hear they made a change.  The menu is also very limited with choices of toppings.  They offer a veggie pizza but do not have broccoli or spinach.   I am only giving them the 2 stars because of the person I spoke with, I hope they find a new delivery service and then advertise that on their web site when the do.

I have mixed feelings about Angelo's. I like the NY style Pizza, thin crust, it's not bad. I also like the cheesesteaks though they need to cut back on the salt. But for those positives I thought their Hoagies are simply awful. I had an Italian Hoagie and all I can say was where is the meat? for 6.50 it had less meat than a cheapo wawa hoagie and roll was extremely soggy to boot (disgusting!!!!). While I may go back to the Pizza I'll never order another Hoagie from there.

reviews.text: This place doesn't look like much from the outside, but I've been continually pleased with the food and service each time I visit. They have the best wings and good chicken cheesesteaks. Be aware that there are no waiters; just go to the bar to put your order in. Better yet, just sit at the bar and enjoy the view of some of the 17 flat screen TVs. Definitely a great place to watch a sporting event!

We moved to town and just recently stopped in for the 1st time. I was very happy with how clean the place was. The bartenders were nice and welcoming. Beer list was solid. The bar menu looks great; lots of traditional bar food choices and also some interesting, different things. We had wings in AC sauce and they were SO good. Juicy and crispy, and the sauce was absolutely delish. Fried shrimp in hot sauce were also great. We live in walking distance and will be back soon.

It's a dive bar where all the shader alcoholics go...The food is your typical bar slop, the more you eat the fatter you get...The bartenders are very friendly with the regulars, they'll have your drink waiting for you and they order beers that their regulars drink. Late night Fridays and Saturdays are always enjoyable to people watch because the freaks really do come out at night...

reviews.text:
Mt. Fuji is our new favorite place when we don't feel like we want to cook (and that does not really happen lately besides some weekends).  The hubs and I have been here a long, long time ago for the sushi and even before the place expanded, but don't remember if the sushi was good or not. 

We love the hibachi here. Hibachi is always pricey (~$25), but so good and makes for great leftovers.  Husband gets the filet mignon with scallops and I get filet mignon with salmon.  Sometimes we get a shrimp or two from the chef. Hibachi comes with a small soup and salad. 

Sushi is a hit or miss, as are the appetizers.  We tend to stick with just the good ol' hibachi and always look forward to the "yum yum" sauce to dip everything in - is that weird?  The "yum yum" sauce here tastes better than other hibachi places we have been to.  If you like it as much as us, you'll be excited to know that the salad comes with "yum yum" sauce as well. 

So happy to see that Mt. Fuji has expanded in this not-so-poppin' plaza and seems to have very good business.  Definitely one of the few places in our dinner rotation! 

P.S. Our baby daughter drools every time we go here, hehe.  She will be thrilled to eat with us when she gets older!
Paid extra for sea scallops and got real thin fake scallops all were the same size . Sea scallops are all different thicknesses and also have a sweet taste not like the tasteless ones i was served

There is a lot to be said for consistency. This place always makes solid sushi, the fish is fresh and I don't know anyone who has gotten sick from eating there, unlike 99% of the other Japanese restaurants in and around the Camden/Gloucester/Philadelphia counties that aren't super pricey. 
On Sundays they have AYCE and the quality is still there. Unless you're looking for an omakase treat, this is the spot for sushi at a reasonable price.

reviews.text: One of my favorite Pho spots to go to.  The place is clean, parking is convenient, and the food is pretty good too.  I especially love their beef stew pho.  The stewed beef just melts in your mouth, it is so tender and yummy.

after reading reviews, we met the same , tried to ask about the menu, ignored us, insisted I order the pho, since it was late and saw it was busy, I said ok. menu prices are wrong , surprised he didn't tell us, yelled at us

My go to pho place since coming to Philly.  Generous portions, good hours.  Just be careful late nights on wkends but they can run out of soup!!  Cash only unless over $10 which isn't an issue if you also get their super delicious avocado smoothie to lessen the spiciness when you add too much sriracha or their vietnamese coffee with condensed milkehcih surpasses anything Starbucks or La Colombe can come up with.

reviews.text:
Of the many Panera Breads I've been to (some even better in the area) this one ranks lowly on the scale of greatness.

All times that I have been to this Panera the staff are unfriendly, rude, act like they don't give a toss about customers or helping them, etc. Customers walk around blindly trying to figure out the most basic elements of a restaurant such as where to pick up your food from, or where to place an order to begin with. Asking the people at the register is useless as they always seem to find themselves too busy to assist customers who need help, and going to the other side where the kitchen is is also useless as these employees are too busy preparing food to provide any assistance to lost customers.

The food is less than average for a Panera Bread. As mentioned above the kitchen is hectic and probably a living hell given the way everyone steps over each other and tries to do their own thing without any kind of cohesion. The managers/supervisors look and sound mean, doesn't look like employees are working together so much as trying to survive the impossible traffic this location receives every day under the poor management.


All in all, skip this location. There are plenty of better eateries accessible around this Panera Bread. Don't give anymore of your hard earned money to this underperforming, poorly managed corporate chain that could easily be replaced with another.

Stopped in here for breakfast and went with the steel cut oatmeal with cinnamon crunch topping and strawberries along with an orange scone and a caramel latte. I would have liked my oatmeal to have been a little more moist, but it wasn't too bad. The orange scone and caramel latte were delicious. Downside for my wife is that there aren't many gluten-free options for breakfast. Even the soufflé, which would normally be a GF option is not here, so she had to stick with the oatmeal and fresh cut fruit. Decor inside was nice with plenty of seating and staff was friendly.

This Panera just opened yesterday.

Now the Providence Towne Center will have a decent breakfast option besides Wegmans and Starbucks.

The Asiago Bagel Egg and Cheese was warm, gooey and delicious.

I suspect this will become a regular morning stop for me. Their other sandwiches and pasta options look good as well. It's need a while since I used to frequent Paneras when I was in Princeton.

reviews.text: Could have been better. Unlike Chinese food at all. No taste soever. Seems like Depending on a persons personality, they serve the quantity and not evenly for everyone.
Great food court food. The  sesame and general tsao chicken were the best. I also had Io mein. Great value platter, would definitely go back again.
This is one of my favorite places in the area. It's super quick, delicious , and cheap. A huge portion of tofu and Lo mein is only $6 total! Also everyone who works there is super friendly.
Ehhh.  First and only time. Won't go back.  The man who made my husband's burrito didn't have gloves on, and scooped and rolled the food bare-handed.   Way way overpriced.

Meh. I was very disappointed this time around. Ground beef tasted like some sort of odd sausage and there was a potato in my taco. The tomatoes where old and the taco shell tasted stale. I would have been better off getting Taco Bell. Definitely won't go back again.

The food is good. Disappointed in the cooks without masks over their noses. Two of them only had it over their mouth; one girl hurried up and put it on when I walked in and the other guy just went about making food. I said something and the cashier was blasé. I know everyone has covid fatigue, but they require customers to wear masks, and they should def be preparing food with masks on. 

Trying real hard to support local businesses during this mess but come on, please comply with guidelines and keep your customers safe. :(

name: Kung Fu Tea
description: Taiwanese, Food, Bubble Tea, Juice Bars & Smoothies, Restaurants, Coffee & Tea

reviews.text:
It takes unique taste buds to enjoy this cold milk bubble tea. It caught me off guard. It reminded me of instant tea we had in the 70s mixed with milk. Then you get surprises with large pieces of tapioca that taste like tea flavored gummies.

I'll come back to try same flavor but HOT. I'm not knocking this. It's worth the experience.

Brand new bubble tea in the area, clean facility, and good service. Love the popcorn chicken and the honey milk tea; altho the sauce for the pop corn chicken was too little and the rice to avocado ratio for the avocado kani was very little avocado filling and a bit more on the rice side. It still taste good tho. Would definitely come back again.

I am a door dasher and today I picked up an order to deliver from this location. the tea leaked........BADLY on my way to the customer's house. I came back to Kung Fu to get a new one. They REFUSED to make the customer a new one! Wouldn't help me at all! I've worked in the restaurant industry for many years at several different restaurants. Every time there was something wrong with a customer's order or something happened to it, the restaurant would always make a new one whether it was their fault or not. Terrible customer service! I will also be complaining to Door Dash about them.

reviews.text: I'm so annoyed that they closed the Delran location so I tried the cherry hill location out and they messed my order up, gave me French baguette instead of the chips I ordered and left the chicken and apple chips  out of my Fuji Apple chicken salad how do you mess that up, I will not be eating at this location again

Assistant manager Rivera
Started 2 weeks ago
Is friendly with a smile
 and doing a great
Job keeping things moving and clean at cherry hill
Glad he's there

This is by far the quickest Panera I've ever been to- the food is ready very, very quickly.

I usually order the U-Pick-2, and get a salad and sandwich. All of the food is very fresh (that can be a problem at other paneras!). The side bread is also very fresh- not that rock-hard, day old stuff.

Depending on who's working, they can be a little lazy. My most recent experience with the Avocado Chicken Cobb Salad was one giant hunk of avocado. Don't get me wrong- I love avocado- but they did nothing to chop it into smaller pieces, which is then a bit difficult to do in the small carry-out containers.

I'd go here again as it's fast, and depending if they change the laziness at points, I'll update my review. Overall, though, the speed of this Panera is amazing.

reviews.text: I've had the bun bo hue and the bun mam. I highly recommend the bun mam, wonderfully seasoned with spices and lemongrass, very aromatic, and filled with herbs. In fact, it's the only dish I get from here every time.

My cousin swears by this place and is a frequent patron. So being that I trust her taste and honesty, I decided to opt for a try. Went with the chicken pho that she highly recommended. Along with egg rolls as appetizer and Banh Uot. 

Egg rolls were good. Nice & crispy with good filling. Now... I'm not into chicken pho, but their broth is good that I can consume without the meat. I wasn't a big fan with their steamed chicken though. I for sure had better elsewhere. Banh Uot was probably my favorite. I had to share with the BF. Their fermented beef was interesting. Had a different taste to the palate than what I'm used too.

I wouldn't mind returning to try other dishes. Maybe the ratings would change, but all in all I'm mutual and give it a solid 3 stars. Still kind of new, so hoping this establishment would progress and grow.
Update: I had the broken rice platter, the summer rolls, and spring rolls & all were fantastic. Usually my go-to place for vietnamese food!

reviews.text:
I usually try to go the non-chain route when it comes to pizza.  However, when I am looking for a speedy delivery and can knock out a quick order online, Domino's fits the bill just fine.  As far as quality goes my family likes their new handmade pan style pizza.  I also like that they have garlic sauce available as a side.  

My experiences here have always been positive whether it be delivery or carry-out.

The prices are low, but the quality is lower.  In these times when businesses are struggling, one would think that the location would want to earn business.  Instead, the staff is impolite.  Perhaps not trained in customer care.  Avoid and support other local businesses instead.

I tried this place again and regretted it again. Placed an order in the afternoon for a 6:20 delivery. They started prepping at 5:50. Put it in the oven at 6:27 and now at 7:10 it's stil quality checking. After being on hold for 50 minutes they hung up on me. This place sucks!! Worst customer service ever. Close them down!!

name: Mr Wish
description: Bubble Tea, Food, Tea Rooms, Juice Bars & Smoothies

reviews.text: Great passion fruit green tea!! Trust me, Mr.Wish will be your final destination of any boba places in Chinatown! Love the taste and bubbles! Definitely will come back soon!

Our favorite bubble tea store whenever we're in Philadelphia. Small and tucked into a corner of Chinatown, this is a cute store with an odd mascot/logo which looks like a molten version of the Bic pen man . The bubble teas are tasty and the boba are perfect, every time.

Went and got the brown sugar pearl special and it was HEAVENLY. If you ever see it offered, would highly recommend. For less than 5 dollars, this drink brought the perfect combination of warm, freshly cooked, brown sugar style pearls that are the perfect consistency of chewy, while also accenting the brown sugar flavor without being too sweet. It is topped with whole milk and a generous portion of the pearls. Absolutely delicious.

reviews.text:
Authentic pho restaurant located in a small Vietnamese shopping area where the wait staff and customers speak Vietnamese.

The large pho IS huge: the bowl is almost a chopstick's length in diameter! The broth is full flavored with not much oil.

The fried spring rolls were golden brown with a nice crisp exterior. However, they had a slightly off flavor, possibly suggesting that the oil they were fried in wasn't as fresh as it could have been.
Very fast service, and excellent.  Lots of turnover.  Today it's harder to park as there is construction, but worth the trip.

Dined and ordered to go from here a couple of times. Great menu selection, reasonably priced (unlike other Vietnamese restaurants that overcharges on pho), and great services. My favorite is their bunbohue and pho dac Biet. The restaurant is located next to an asian supermarket so there is parking available. Definitely recommend this restaurant if you're looking for some good authentic Vietnamese food in the south Philadelphia area!!

reviews.text: The staff are nice but that doesn't compensate for the fact that I've gotten food poising from this place!!!! They don't change their grease so no matter what you order, funnel cake, fries, shrimp they're all going to end up tasting the same.

Ordered shrimp broccoli and rice and they mixed that fake ass chicken with the shrimp and broccoli smh or should I say rat loll anyway they have nasty attitudes . You ask them for something and they act like its a burden . Last time I checked I'm paying my money to eat here !

This place is absolutely THE BEST!! Food is consistently always piping hot and crisp on delivery. Fresh ingredients & packed well for delivery to your door. You won't be disappointed. Give them a play- you will be back again & again!!

reviews.text: The worst Subway I have ever been to in my life. The person who was working there threw the sandwich together with no care at all. Then the taste was so garbage. Ruined my day.

So, I stopped in on a Wednesday afternoon around 2:30 for a late lunch. The place was clean but the order boards seem totally out of wack. It was hard for me to find the different sandwiches listed. The guy behind the counter was pretty rude and unfriendly. I probably won't be going back but the food was fine.

I purchased a very simple ham and cheese sandwich for my kids.  There was a line of workers to keep things moving along somewhere along that line my sandwich was switched with the person next to me.  When I got home my kids sandwich was the totally wrong sandwich.  When I returned to the subway to get a correct order, and asked if they were going to compensate me for the 45 minutes of lost time they simply shook their head no and said they would make me the right sandwich.  Totally unprofessional !!!  People, and this means the owners of this place, should be responsible for their business and the mistakes they make or get out of business.

reviews.text: This Subway is great. The owner Gary is warm and this Subway tastes good. Love the chicken sub there. It is also really clean there and if you need to pick up a few other items there is a convenience store in there as well!

I stopped into this subway for lunch.  Wow!  It was great.  Excellent food and service.  They have a small lounge with a large tv.  Bathroom was spotless and welcoming.  I got two free cookies - probably because I brought my whole family - all 7 of us.  Cost over $60 but worth every penny. We had a really great lunch and enjoyed watching the eagles game at the same time.  Will definitely come back.  Great owner - friendly and knows sports pretty good, but not great.Gary really is terrific.

Quick and courteous service. Convenience store is attached with a nice sitting area with a large TV with the local sports team game on if there is a game on.

The convenience store also serves La Colombe coffee in the morning, and have cold brew coffee available as well in the cooler.

reviews.text:
Joes is weird....let me explain.

I recently got a new job in the area, so I was out scouting new places to eat and happened upon Joes, so I decided to stop in and get some Italian. The first thing that I noticed when I walked in was the latino radio station playing as the 100% latino staff worked the ovens and register. Not a problem, its just that Joes does not read "Italian" in ANY way. Like I said, that doesn't bother me in the slightest; if the food is good, I don't care if clowns cook it, it was just a little weird. 

What DID take me aback is the next thing; are people supposed to be behind the counter?! As I sat, waiting for my food to be ready, a lady got up, walked behind the counter and refilled her soda and went back to her seat. "Ooooookay....she must work here or something, or know the owners...." As I sat, no less than FOUR MORE PEOPLE just walked in, and walked behind the counter. They refilled their drinks, got ice, picked up and touched things, etc. One guy even finished his food, walked behind the counter, GOT CHANGE FOR A 10 FROM THE REGISTER, and left through the back door! And he had like a USPS uniform on, so he absolutely didn't work there. It was SO WEIRD! Is that just like a thing they do here? I'm confused.

About the food, I had pizza the night before, so I went with chicken fingers at Joes. The fries were perfect, and the chicken was cooked well enough, even though they were less "fingers" and more "flat pounded chicken." The fingers weren't really seasoned and I asked for honey mustard to eat them with. The honey mustard was TERRIBLE. It tasted like old wax or something, and I'm almost positive there was no "mustard" in it. It was like, mayonnaise, honey and tortured souls. Yuck. 

Chicken fingers, fries, drinks and side of regret flavored like honey mustard came to about $10.

The good news is I didn't wait long for my cheesesteak,  The bad news is the cheese wasn't melted well and the mushrooms got very little/no grill time.  The pizza looked amazing and they had a steady flow of regulars.

The plain cheese pizza is too doughy,not crispy at all and soggy although what I had was reheated leftover slice I will say I won't be in any rush to try this again. 

Limited pizza options out this way may have me circle back to trying another slice, but so far Marino's may be the more consistently good pie that delivers out here for now.

reviews.text:
I just moved to the area and was looking for a new Chinese restaurant to frequent. I ordered lunch take out and was left really wanting. 

I ordered the wonton soup and general tso chicken. My order was ready very shortly after I arrived and was hot and packed nicely. 

I got home and dug into the soup, the wantons were very good and I was hopeful for the rest of my meal. However, I should have stopped with the soup. There was nothing appealing about my chicken dish at all. The rice was flavorless and the broccoli tasted frozen microwaved. The chicken had nice color but what sauce was on the chicken was the consistency of peanut butter and was extremely bland.

chinese has become mine and my husband's sunday night tradition and we always get it from here...helps they're right around the corner. really great bc of how fast they are "10 mineh" all food i've had here has been satisfactory including chicken lo mein, sesame chicken, general tso chicken, steamed dumplings, and egg rolls.
I order the General Tso chicken combo. The chicken is spicy and tender and all white meat. The rice is always terrific and the portion just right. The garlic chicken is   Tasty and not too garlicky.

reviews.text: This little gem surprised me ! The chicken is fresh and has a amazing batter taste. I was suprise to find the batter was different from item to item . The wings vs tenders had a different taste , both of which are amazing . The wings didn't come with a sauce and they didn't need any ! The prices are super reasonable and the restaurant itself was super clean ! They have a nice range of sizes depending on if your dining for one or for a group . Check out this checked ! You won't be disappointed:)

I haven't had fried chicken in a loooong time!
This is a little place on the corner and is kinda no frills.
I can't complain about the chicken though because it was juicy, plump and tasty!
We also opted for the potato wedges which were great!  They were full wedges and were fresh and not greasy!
This is a take out only place and they were a little skimpy with the napkins and the ketchup!

They need to get some dam actually kitchen workers instead of these 15 year old boys, they can't handle the heat in the kitchen when I ask for a simple order they say "we're too busy" lost my business a lot of time because their unprofessional attitude

reviews.text:
Went out our way here to experience and enjoy hot pot from a fresh Vietnamese eatery, what a disappointment. Unfortunately hot pot isn't serve until 4pm, only appetizers and breakfast was available and I arrived at 3pm :( 

Server also did not know what sriracha was. Very confuse about that.

Came here on a Sunday afternoon for lunch with hubby. He ordered the pork chop rice. I asked the waiter what one of the photo I pointed to was and he said " mango chicken salad". I said ok, I'll try it but I specifically asked if they put peanuts on it, he said no, but just in case I asked him to please make sure there's no peanuts. Many Vietnamese dishes love to top their dishes with peanuts. Hubby got his dish and he said it was average. Few minutes after he got his, I got my mango salad, with peanuts . They took it back and made another one. The mango had a nice crunch to it. After about my 3rd piece I realize, there was no chicken. I asked my hubby if I heard it wrong and he agreed that the waiter did mention there was chicken in it. I didn't want to send it back again. I just ate the mango dish and left it at that. Between the mango salad (which is quite a small dish) and his pork chop rice with viet coffee, it cost close to $30. Maybe the waiter didn't familiarize all the dishes yet. But I can give it another try for their hot pot next time :) as for their dishes, in my opinion, it tasted like any viet dish I've had around.

This place use to be International Smokeless BBQ. You can still ordered hot pot but also you can have Vietnamese style breakfast. Stopped here for a late lunch with my Mom. I ordered the deluxe breakfast with steak, meatballs and pate with eggs. It comes with fries and a roll for dipping. It was delicious! And $10 for all that food was definitely worth it. My Mom ordered a noodle dish. It was lacking flavor. But I will let them pass since they just opened. I will definitely bring my entire family here for breakfast. It has plenty of options for the whole family.
