What a bad experience!! Was hesitating putting a bad review, as I really don't like doing that .... but after being stuck in my bathroom with food poisoning from eating an early lunch here today ... I had to let the chain know that something was off with their ingredients today and to be more careful with their future customers ... and nothing. All they said is perhaps you ate elsewhere. Sadly, I didn't. All I had today was a mini American from here at 11 am and ran home from work at 5 with a super crampy and queasy stomach ... here I am shivering and stuck in my bathroom with horrendous food poisoning three hours after getting home. Ughh first and last for me!

We are always on the lookout for a quality sandwich place near our home. This would have been really convenient, and we'd have been overjoyed to like this place. Unfortunately, we were really disappointed.

We got regular size hoagies that look nothing like the photo they show on their website. They said one sandwich would "feed 2 people" for almost $10 with tax. What 2 people do you know who will eat 3.5" of sandwich for a meal and be satisfied? Not two grown-adult non-anorexic Philadelphians. Was this a mistake by a new employee or something?

This place is new, and I try to pad reviews for newer places even when I don't dig them, but in this case, I could not finish eating my meal, so I can't ignore that.

Just under $19 for two 7" hoagies that were Wawa quality, from roll, to meats, to mayo.

In fairness, I am not a chain hoagie person. If you like places like Primo's, Subway or Wawa, then by all means, help yourself to Jersey Mike's. But if you are more of a mom-n-pop authentic Philly sandwich type of person, who has come to know the quality meats, toppings and rolls that our area has to offer, then I don't think the quality at this place will stand up to what you're used to.

We had a turkey hoagie and an Italian, both were very low-quality meats. Also, the veggies were tasteless and the roll was terrible. It was definitely the kind of roll you'd get at Subway, not at all something that tasted fresh from a Philly bakery.

My turkey was the same rubbery-looking stuff they give you at Wawa. I could not finish. Wasted half the sandwich, which was only 7 measly inches to begin with.

The Italian was no better. Not much flavor, all lower-quality ingredients. Thinly-packed, with not much in it at all. Again, very disappointing.

They put a lot of hype into their marketing and advertising, and have fancy logo-printed wax paper and bags. The bag and wax paper presentation was like Burger King. Please, save the money on the logos and put it into better quality ingredients. To us, you just branded something we will never eat again, and couldn't finish. Wasted money. Had to go out again to get takeout elsewhere just to finish dinner.

Sorry Jersey Mike's, we heard great things about you on Philly.com and thought you'd be different from Primo's. I guess a franchise, is a franchise, is a franchise. It's just not for us.

reviews.text: Ordered a few times, never had an issue. I prefer the taste of this bread and the freshness to a Wawa sub any day. I like the Oil/Vinegar, etc. I wish there were more of them around to be honest. The packaging where they wrap it up as pretty convenient as well. I cant really rate the store as I have not been in there in a long time, but the deliveries have been fine.

Same fresh food and nice staff as one of their other stores not quite as fast as the other store I visited but place was immaculate and conveniently located next to Starbucks. 
We love the oil vinegar mixture on the Italian.
They were running some special on subs since they just opened and we were happy to find out we got our meals for like 2 bucks!!!! 
It does appear someone here is community minded as they according to my information work with MS of Delaware I believe .. 
That's nice to see and made me a loyal customer. You guys are the best thanks a lot!!!!

Wow! I went to Jersey Mike's for the first time today. I must say that it is my new go to sub and cheesesteak joint. They did everything right. The establishment was clean, the staff friendly and conscientious, and the food was amazing. I did a couple substitutions, and it was no issue, and completed to perfection. Way to go Jersey Mike's staff!

reviews.text: Pretty good quality sushi at a decent price! Sad they don't deliver, they'd make BANK.

I was recently at Ooka down the road and would actually rather Sushi House.  The dining room is small, so I usually get take out.  I'm nothing of a sushi expert, but it's definitely worth a try at the least.

Great sushi at an even better price! The pink lady was phenomenal. Grilled calamari was excellent and was a very different take on it. Service was perfect, everything was from deinks to desert were all right on time. Fish was very fresh.

name: Krispy Krunchy Chicken
description: Sandwiches, Restaurants, Halal, Fast Food, Chicken Wings, Chicken Shop

reviews.text: Being as though this place is located inside a gas station, I was skeptical lol I actually was delivering for Uber eats how I ended up trying the place. They were so nice! Great service. Gave me a free sample of their chicken tenders.... was blown away! Was sooo good. Now it's my go to fried chicken place. The best as wild as that sounds. Try it!
Awful service. Messed up my order and refused to apologize or correct it. Very very disappointing

Well the name says it all and I was pretty impressed. I don't remember when gas station chicken became a thing but a friend turned me on to Royal Farms years ago. I did some googling and found out this is a very southern thing and that Krispy Krunchy Chicken is kind of a big deal down there. I was shocked to find one so close. I never noticed it because I don't use the Exxon station it operates out of.

They have stand inside and a menu full of combos and options. The chicken looked damn good. The sides I was a little iffy about so I got the $5.00 tenders special. I didn't know how many tenders I was getting but it came with fries and a biscuit. The nice man put my meal together and off I went with pretty stuffed little platter. Don't hesitate if you're craving fried chicken and see this stand at your gas station.

reviews.text:
Golden Key is the best Chinese restaurant in the area. I drive best multiple Chinese restaurants just to eat here. They have good customer service, and have your food ready quickly and correctly. 
The food is seasoned and flavorful. The meat dishes are hearty and has a nice bite of meat without tons of breading. The dishes such as the general tso's chicken, etc is cooked very well with a nice crisp to it without over doing it. 
They deliver within a wide distance and are very quick with their deliveries. They are a nice, clean establishment. I would recommend this Chinese restaurant to anyone looking for some delicious Chinese takeout in the area.

We ordered food at 9 on a Sat night.  They said 45-50 mins, which I was surprised at the estimated time.  The food was delivered in about 15 mins and it was snowing at that time.  I didn't know they had online ordering and it would have benefitted us as I inquired about the $1 pancake on the menu and she said it was $4 and I said no thanks as I just wanted to see but they still sent it to us, but it was work it (scallion pancakes with dipping sauce... very good, but flimsy which is fine if you dont mind it.  The wonton soup was very good, excellent broth, very good wontons.  The egg rolls were solid.  Almost an hour had passed by the time I got to my container of chicken lo mein and pork fried rice and it was still very hot, which really surprised me and it was quite good.  We have a ton of leftovers and can't wait to eat them.  Overall food was between good and very good and the 15 min turn time in the snow was what cemented a 4 star rating.  I have ordered here before and enjoyed it.  Will make this my Chinese food delivery spot now.

The food was alright.  Not the stellar Chinese one is always looking for.  The flavors were pretty good but I found all the food greasy.  Pork ribs were tasty until you got to a grisly part.  Not so yummy when you have to spit your food out.  The wonton soup had a lemony taste to the broth - weird.

reviews.text: They are skimpy on sandwich toppings.  I had to ask numerous times and then the sandwich maker would put a small pinch on.  If you want a sandwich made how you like it dont go here.

It's a Subway, so you know the drill. I'm only docking stars for this location on account of its overall atmosphere and the service. Aside from that, the sandwiches are exactly the same as at every other Subway on the planet.

Also, they haven't kicked on the A/C yet. I mean, I know it costs money, but seriously. It's like 90 degrees out.

My husband and I take turns stopping in on the weekends for their egg flatbreads. They guy who works in the morning on the weekend is great -- friendly, efficient, and remembered us and our orders after a couple visits.

name: Miraku Japanese Restaurant
description: Event Planning & Services, Japanese, Restaurants, Caterers

reviews.text: I sure hope I didn't close!!! This was my favorite sushi place for the ambiance and very fresh sushi.  Can't beat the decor.  Pricier than many local joints, but worth going c/ c it is a notch or two above the milieu.
Not as urban/hip as an Ooka, but I've eaten here about ten times and it's always been reliable. Decent decor, definitely does not feel like a strip mall "joint".

I've been going here on and off for the past 6 years. There has been some major and minor changes and I stuck with Miraku through thick and thin. Overall, I go back to Miraku because their sushi is one of the freshest I've ever tasted. I am not a big fan of maki(rolls) but Miraku's specialty makis are really good. Especially the double spicy salmon roll(YUM), the snow storm roll(torched yellow tail with spicy tuna, double YUM), and the lobster roll(with uni sauce? PERFECTO). 

The kitchen food(hot foo) is sometimes hit or miss but when it's right, it's SO right. They change the presentation and ingredients often. I consider it to be a positive thing because they're constantly striving to be better. 

The servers aren't your average snobby city servers - they all seem to be either in high school or college. It's always been like that. Though I enjoy the full proper service when dining out, I feel like I can relax here and the servers are really cute running around and doing what they can do best to make your dinner more memorable. 

PS. it's a BYOB so bring your favorite sake and ask them to heat it up. You'll have perfectly warm/hot sake to go with delicious sushi. Also, I found that Miraku is cheaper when it comes to the toros - O toro or Chu toro. 

PSS. The wooden decor is really pretty. They also have private rooms for the big parties... of 6 or more.

reviews.text: The lady who works in subway has a bad attitude problem. We arrived at 7.43 pm today Sunday we ordered our order and told her we want dinning here, she replied back I am closing soon so please complete fast your food fast straight on my face and she switch off all lights at 7.45 pm . So no customer can come and those where present their need to get out. Secondly she has no smile it customer communication.Owner should really take an action or else he will loose his/her business.

I had a 6 inch tuna fish sandwich with cheese potato chips and a drink for lunch. The staff was friendly. I received my food fairly quickly, and the price of $8 was very reasonable.  The food was delicious and I enjoyed it. 

There is a large parking lot in front of the store, which is located on a corner of an intersection.  The subway store was clean.
This place has the best pizza ,I will give 10 out of 10 and I will give 1 out of 10 to their persian food .Please stick with pizza only .The atmosphere is great and our service was great .

name: Subway
description: Fast Food, Sandwiches, Restaurants, Salad, American (Traditional)

reviews.text: I've always had good experiences here, and I go here a lot. Nice employees, and the food is always good. They've made special orders for me and gone out of their way to give good customer service. Highly recommend this location!

I was there today at 1130am getting some food. Ordered a sub and the guy doesn't ask if I wanted it toasted even though I did. Then one of the wall menus fell to the ground which is a representation of this subway location..anyways, he then picks up the sign with his gloves and then proceeds to start handling my sub and puts my toppings on my sub.  Like come on, you kidding me. I wish I was a food inspector so I could fire him right then and there.  I asked him to change the gloves and he said no no it's fine.  I said dude, no I dont want to get sick from that. He made me another sub like a little beep and wasn't very nice about it.  Wont be going there ever again.  Wasting my hard earned money for that bs..forget that.

For the positive, the location is clean. I ordered sandwiches using the Subway app, which allows you to request more or less of ingredients. I asked for more of almost all vegetables, and there were maybe 4 pieces total (of each) on a foot long sub of onions, green peppers, and banana peppers, and barely any lettuce and spinach. Scrawniest sandwich I've ever gotten from a Subway.

name: Mr. Wish
description: Taiwanese, Bubble Tea, Food, Restaurants, Juice Bars & Smoothies

reviews.text:
It was our first time at Mr. Wish and it was really good! The service was fast, and the employees were helpful and of course what my sister and I got both was really tasty and refreshing. We told them it was our first time, and they said they use all fresh fruit and everything they have is refreshing. 

I got a mango smoothie, which only comes in a medium size and it had small chunks of frozen mango. The medium was a good size but it was $4.75, which is a bit expensive. 

My sister got the mango tea with fresh pulp in the large size. She asked for boba pearls which was 75¢ extra for the topping, so hers ended up being $6.25 but the large is a good size. My sister says it was very fresh. 

Inside the actual store front it was a good size, not too big and not too small. It had some tables and chairs to wait or sit and eat in. I was able to pay with my card, and tip on their iPad and text the receipt to my phone easy peasy. Overall I would go back again,   especially because the location was close to my house. There are also a lot of other locations near my house, which speaks to their popularity in the area. 10/10

Sure you may have to wait a little longer when it's busy, but the drinks are worth it. Probably the best Mr. Wish I've been to actually. The Mango smoothie is made with care and you can actually taste the fresh mango. Plus the staff is pleasant, which makes a world of difference too. I'm sure they will grow their staff with time since they just opened.
Came here a few times already. They're consistent, friendly, and just what you'd expect from a bubble tea spot. Great environment, clean establishment, can't go wrong.

reviews.text: The best wings anywhere.   A great selection of sauces that are amazing and they never let me down. The only place I order wings from
Terribly slow! So far I'm here for about 15 minutes and still no wings. Placed an order of 24 wings with two different sauces and will update after I actually get the food

Great place. Prices are a bit higher than others, but it's worth it. I highly recommend their suicide sauce; it's really good, and hot enough to be fun without painful. I've also tried "Extra Hot", which is really good as well. They wouldn't let me get homicide unless I had tried it before... which seems like a catch 22. I'm not sure it even exists. 

The two guys who work there are really nice and friendly. I'm never waiting very long, and the TV is usually tuned in to the news or whatever sports game is on.

They have two tables,  but I don't think you're meant to eat in (it is wings TO GO after all). 

Overall my favorite wings place in the area. And they're right across the parking lot from PIzza City and a liquor store, which is really convenient.

All of the food was wonderful and we really enjoyed our meal! 
If you want great old school take out school Chinese food order from Wok And Roll.

First time here, tonight(3/17/13).  Sister lives nearby and wanted to come here for dinner. We are both vegetarians, so I ordered the Gen. Tsos Bean Curds because she said it was good, n boy was she right! The tofu was nice n crisp outside, and not mushy. The sauce was sweet n spicy, just right. The food was piping hot. My nephew ate honey chicken with pork fried rice, but i couldn't see the pork, LOL. He said the chicken was really good, n his eggroll likewise. I also had hot n sour soup, which was delicious as not many places can make it good. I ordered a scallion pancake which my SIS liked, but i thought was just a Lil too doughy for me, but dipping sauce was good. SIS n i both had springrolls, n she devoured hers, n i will eat mine with my leftovers. N this establishment happens to have brown rice, which I prefer over white rice. Overall, I was pleased n impressed, as initial impression was...I sure hope their food is good. I will definitely be back, n i added them to yelp so others can enjoy their food too!!!!

I LOVE, LOVE, LOVE pumpkin pie. I hate when it's covered in so much spice or so sickeningly sweet that it is more like pumpkin laced sugar. I am particular about the crust too and expect that to be flavorful, crisp, and just the right amount of crunch on the top. I wasn't planning on purchasing a pumpkin pie for thanksgiving, but as I walked down the aisle of my local organic market, I saw this gem of a pumpkin pie and it was calling my name. Imagine my delight when I opened and bit into my first slice only to realize this was to become my favorite pumpkin pie - ever. Seriously, it was that good! For $14.95 (which I didn't think is unreasonable for a good quality pie), this pie was worth every penny! I need another please, stat!!!

Absolutely terrible!  Should be 0 stars or less.  Single employee running this Subway at the Plymouth Meeting Mall was incompetent, incapable and an idiot at lunchtime on 7/14/21.  I ordered a 6" turkey with American cheese and a little Mayo.  He maimed the bread cutting it incompletely and then 'finished' the job ripping it open with his hands.  Threw the turkey & cheese on the bread and then squeezed a huge amount of Mayo on it.  I also ordered 2 plain soft pretzels and repeatedly told him no cinnamon.  As you might guess the pretzels had cinnamon on them.  He moved at glacial speed.  Why I paid for this slop is beyond me.

I ordered Yang Zhou fried rice last night and 2 orders of the wonton soup + wonton egg drop soup.. Yang zhou fried rice was amazing and delicious, very tasty and flavorful with delicious roast pork, chicken and shrimp. .

On the wonton, the meat part are tasty and delicious. The wonton skin, i am not used to with thick wonton skin and i wish they use thinner wonton skin.

The egg drop soup are amazing: 

Surely love and will try more of their food again..

Good food and fast delivery. We recently moved to this area and were looking for a good chinese restaurant. This place did not disappoint to satisfy a craving. I will say I have had better chinese food, but as far as the few places we've tried in this area, China Wok is pretty good.
Ordered Vegetable LoMien, Crab Rangoon and Egg-rolls. Everything was great, best Chinese food in the area.

reviews.text: Yummy Cheesy Pizza! If you like soft doughy pizza with lots of cheese order from here. I've never been to the restaurant but have had delivery several times.  Never had any issues with wrong orders or bad food.

The girls at the front are unbelievably rude. It's unfortunate since the food is delicious. I am sitting waiting for my food and the girls are hanging up on customers, yelling at each other, dropping the F bomb like it's allowed, and telling customers on the phone "don't give me attitude". I have worked in food service for years and can not believe that this kind of behavior is allowed. Not to mention the coughing all over the air, hands, and FOOD. Such a shame that I won't be coming back, because I love the food

My wife and I came here because the pizza place we normally went to was no longer in business... We were looking for another place to go to and found Angelo's... The pizza was absolutely delicious and the staff was friendly and helpful... If you're looking for good  pizza and you're in the Riverside area this is the place to go...

reviews.text: My bread was so stale it broke n flaked off as I picked my sandwich up. I couldn't even eat my sandwich because the bread was so bad

The wait staff was surly, didn't know the difference between a sweet pepper and pickled pepper. They ran out of water cups so we couldn't have water with our meal. 

They were rude when we asked for salt after the sandwich stating, " you didn't ask for it". 

One worker spent her time texting on he cell phone while the other did minimal work.

I wouldn't eat at this subway ever again!
Owner is very nice. The store has had a cash only sign up for awhile, not sure if they are attempting to cut back on the fee the store pays for cards or if the machine is really broken.

reviews.text: Food is always great. Hot and sour soup there is a lot different than other places. Tastes really good. It's Chinese food (duh!) so expect it to have grease. I can assure that all Chinese food has grease, so I don't know what the complaint is about grease... anyways I think it's less greasier than your average Chinese food in the corner.
Food is very bland, the guy who works there is kinda rude. Don't waste your time like I did 2x!

Even though I am Chinese and I eat Chinese food alomost everyday, I still like this place. I like rice noodles most, orient express had the tastiest Singapore rice noodles I have, the taste of curry is not strong. There are chicken, pork abd shrimp but I just like shrimps. The other item I ordered was the shrimp udon, I just dont like the brocolli, and I like it spicy. 

Just sometimes you have to wait a little longer for them to make the food.

reviews.text: Obviously if you have eaten at subway before the food is the same at every location the difference is the staff.  This subway is HORRIBLE for service.  They have two girls that work there that are friendly and polite.  Every other girl they have working there is just down right rude.  One girl even tries to put less meat on your sandwich if she thinks you are not looking.  They act like it is an inconvenience if you have to ask them what kind of soup they have but you always have to ask because they never update the board that tells you.  I, unfortunatly, am stuck going to this location if I want subway for lunch because I only have a short lunch break and this is the only location that I am able to make it to in my time frame.  If you are able to avoid this subway I would definatly reccomend finding a different location.

Amazing service and great fresh food . Haven't seen anywhere else where an employee would come to the table and offer soda refills ... 
Good job keep it up guys .

I had a meeting in south philly today and lunch was catered by Subway. At first I felt let down that I'm in south philly with all these great sandwich places and I'm stuck eating subway. But boy was I wrong. The food was do good and I loved the lunch box they served it in. Also the cookie was so tasty. I have to admit that subway has upped their game and food was even better than panera and Corner bakery were we usually cater from in our blue bell office.

reviews.text:
Parking is horrible, bathroom cleanliness is questionable, but location is somewhat good and it is the same old subway.

What really sucks is the service.  English of the people behind the counter is far from proficiency in both speaking and understanding.  They will hold the line to count off the slices, I guess they care more to save a portion of a cent on a slice of salami.

Once a teenage guy served me there, he was much better at being speedy and did not care to split occasional piece of salami in two.

It's pretty difficult to get making a sub wrong, so the food was fine. 
The service was also very prompt and friendly as well. 
Will come back again.

This place sucks!!! Store #2376 sells stale bread for sandwiches.  Apparently, this location has changed hands since 2014 because this location bakes their bread at 10am in the morning and sells it all day without baking more.  When I got there at 4:38pm asked for wheat bread and wanted the roll scooped.  When guy scooped bread it began to fall apart but if roll were fresh it would not have done so.  I questioned the guy and he told me they only bake bread at 10am.  The bread sits inside of the oven which is off.  The ends of the bread were hard.  Stay away from this location as the lunch meat also looked old.  I know there are better quality Subway's you will just have to find one.

name: Cafe Con Leche
description: Sandwiches, Diners, American (New), Restaurants, Coffee & Tea, Food

reviews.text: Seems to have faded. Food used to be good but last two times everything we had was bland, tasteless and felt microwaved.

This was a tasty bite. My meal started with a sweet potato/jalapeño soup, followed by orange duck, and finished with an Argentinian Chocolate Cake accompanied with a Café con Leche. This dinner stop did lived up to its reviews. The restaurant is a cute quaint establishment. Their menu has numerous traditional choices, vegetarian dishes, and gluten free options. The soup was hearty, the entree was well executed, to include the potato mash and grilled vegetables. This chocolate cake slice was massive and pretty unique. It had layered puff pasty and dulce de leche. I'm kind of picky with my coffee and this café con leche was spot on. So sad I'm in town for only a few days, I would love to go back and try other item from their menu. Good Job Café con Leche!

Great menu and awesome fresh food! The vegan options are plenty and the daily specials menu has several vegan offerings. I had the mole vegan burrito and it was an absolute mouth orgasm! 
Sandi had the stir fry with Blackened Seitan and linguine and Sis had Penne and Broccoli. Rave reviews from all. Will definitely hit here every time I visit my Sister!

reviews.text:
I used to have Jersey Mike's Subs often when I lived in So Cal. I really enjoy the taste and texture of Jersey Mike's! I was happy to be able to enjoy a sub again while visiting family. And thanks to Yelp, I discovered their was a location not far from our hotel! 

I ordered a medium Italian sub with rosemary oregano bread. I didn't have it "the mike's way" (lettuce, tomato, mayo). I had lettuce, tomato, pickles, banana peppers, oil, vinegar, oregano and for some reason I asked for parmesan cheese. Still can't figure that out. 

The sub was just as yummy as I remember. I also ordered a chocolate chip cookie which was the bomb dot com and so soft! I ate it the next morning and it didn't need to be warmed up, it was still soft!

I gave 4 stars because it's a bit pricey. I ordered a medium sub and cookie and it was $12 and something cents plus tip.

I've been to a lot of Jersey Mikes locations and this was the worst one I've ever been to. I arrived and there was one person in front of me. When they got to my order, there were 2 associates working behind the counter. The male associate made one of my sandwiches, then before he made my second one he started a big online order of sandwiches. Unbelievable. So I had to stand there and wait until he made the online order before he got to my second sandwich. And this guy was super slow. Then, finally, he started with the second sandwich. A pen was on the counter and touched my bread! I couldn't believe that. That is beyond dirty. Then I witnessed another associate pick up that pen, use it WITH GLOVES ON, THEN MADE ANOTHER PERSON'S SANDWICH WITH THE SAME GLOVES ON AFTER TOUCHING THE PEN! Again, unbelievable. When I asked for toppings on the side to go, the male associate started packing them, but right in the middle of it a phone rang. He answered the phone WITH GLOVES ON, then DIPPED HIS HANDS BACK INTO THE TOPPINGS WITH THOSE SAME GLOVES ON!! Yuck!!!! So unsanitary!! Needless to say, I threw away those toppings on the side. I spent $20 and will never go back. What a horrible experience. Stay away from this place.
Aaron and Nick are the man! Stayed open late to make the entire Stevens Men's Volleyball team subs.

name: Panera Bread
description: Sandwiches, Restaurants, Soup, Breakfast & Brunch, Bagels, Food, Salad, Bakeries, American (New)

reviews.text: Very disappointed with my recent order here. The Mac & cheese was NOT of the same standard. Hardly any cheese at all! No croutons in the tomato soup & everything else was just slopped together. For the amount they charge I'd expect the high quality Panera was known for.
Nothing to say about it but it's good for the chain. I like to go when I'm craving a different salad.

I was in Panera Bread last week to take my grandparents out to lunch. I ate the Fuji apple chicken salad. OH MY GOD! I loved it. I am a huge fan of composed salads and this did not let me down. My grand mother had the Mediterranean sandwich and my grand father had a cup of french onion soup and a half a tuna sandwich. Both of them cleaned their plates. Which was a surprise to me because they are very hard to please when it comes to food. They both keep kosher (as much as possible when eating out) and both have set diets. And also my grandfather is just a pain in the butt most of them time with how he likes to eat. 

I would have rated them better but the girl who took care of us seemed annoyed when my grandparents asked questions about the food to make sure that things were seasoned to where they could eat it. I understand it was lunch time and it was busy but seriously the girl knew what she signed up for when taking that job. If you can not handle a customer service position then don't work it. She got the order right which was good but her "really I have to do this" attitude had to go.

The wifi did not really work. And my cellphone reception was terrible. I get some anxiety when my son is in school and I do not have cell service. Definitely something they would look into. 

I think the next time I go there it will be for a to go order.

reviews.text: Better than Temple Star. The food was delicious and I got a free iced tea and fortune cookies with my order.

Forget about those other China Houses. Lose that Temple Star take-out menu. Temple's China House on Cecil B. is THE Chinese take-out joint.

I'm sure you, the consumer, are wondering what makes this particular Chinese restaurant--this particular China House--so special. Do they offer anything astoundingly different from the others? No. They just do it really well.

China House is convenient and fast. The General Tso's chicken, most people's go-to, is crispy and well-sauced. The hot and sour soup, my go-to as a starter or entree usually, is appropriately sour and hot, and very chunky. Fried dumplings are delicious. My good friend and former roommate swears by their vegetarian options, particularly the General Tso's Tofu.

As an added bonus, they'll often have SEPTA one-day passes for a dollar off, and even better, they now sell bottles of that ineffable rooster-branded hot sauce, Sriracha. If you live at, or near, Temple, China House ought to be your go-to. If only they were open as late as some of those lesser Chinese places, they could truly be top dog.

The best General Tso at a Chinese take-out I have ever had. I've never tasted better. The chicken is very tender and the sauce does not over power your taste buds. I've constantly recommended the Tso and never have I been given a negative review about it.

reviews.text: I saw an ad for The Spot on Facebook and saw they were offering pickle sandwiches! As someone who LOVES pickles, I knew I had to go! Their food is amazing. Within a week we have gone twice! We have found our new favorite spot. They have something for everyone, delicious offerings, and a great location. With affordable prices and awesome, unique selections, which are all delicious. I would highly recommend the pickle sandwiches or the Buffalo chicken sandwich! A must have when visiting new hope!
This place was awesome when they served burgers! They also had gluten free buns. We were so upset when they moved and completely changed their menu. Please bring back the GF options!!!!

I was sad to see that Moo left this location, but excited to try The Spot after hearing that it was run by some of the Moo staff and who made similar food and kept the same great principles as Moo. Frankly, I think The Spot is a step up from the old restaurant. My husband and I enjoyed delicious burgers,, and split a salad and waffles fries. Everything was amazing and I can't wait to be back. There are vegan and gluten free options too making a  great choice for anyone!

reviews.text: I work in the same shopping center and always find myself walking into Panera. The morning freshly brewed coffee is always a plus, and the breakfast pastries are a nice jumpstart to my day!

Two weekends in a row, we've ordered pick-up dinner from this Panera location.  Both times the order was wrong. On each occasion items were missing. Tonight we were informed they had no bread bowls - a sandwich was missing and the rolls they sent to accompany the soup we ordered were crappy dinner rolls. NOT what we expect from Panera. There was an interesting " Newtown Square" attitude from the workers too. This location needs to get a clue. We won't be back.
Friendly staff, quick efficient service, and located conveniently in an awesome shopping center. I think this Panera is a great option to stop for lunch if you're out and about running errands.

name: Tutti Frutti Frozen Yogurt
description: Ice Cream & Frozen Yogurt, Food, Bakeries, Professional Services

reviews.text: omg im such a frozen yogurt junkie. this place has everything u could ever want. personally, most flavors are too sweet for me...i like the original tart  with fruit toppings.

there was like a tangerine flavor that came bright bright neon orange. I was like mmmm, ok---ay.... unsure. paired that with the weird multicolored jellies and it was yummy. 

The acai blueberry was very creamy and tart and delicious. 

Birthday cake flavor also great. The toppings on the wall are in a container that makes it harder to control the amount you put in your cup which I hate since you pay by weight. But I couldn't resist putting jelly beans in my cup. 

So the selection of different toppings here is great. But if you want higher end quality, yogorino is the way to go.
Yeeeeaaaaahhh...this is gonna be a probem.

The issue here is that this is the best place in the area, but if it were near Temple's main campus it would be very mediocre. Having said that, its still good and cheap. 

The people who work there are really nice. You get a lot of weird people in there, though. Its usually pretty busy, as its the most popular place around. 

About the menu? They have the same as any other chinese takeout place. I happened to like their beef dishes a lot, while the chicken ones weren't that great. Don't waste your time with eggrolls or wonton soup because they don't jack inside.

North Philly is an automatic -2 stars.  If you want chinese food, and go to either temple med or temple dental, this is your only choice.  Variety is good though.  I mean there are all the food carts and stuff around, but if you want "sorta" chinese food then, again, your only choice.

It's not bad.  Don't expect real chinese food.  This is american chinese food.  This place is pretty ghetto.  They have bullet-proof glass up.  Its North philly...

But I mean its pretty cheap, and the quality is decent.  The service is amazingly slow, and honestly you don't to be staying there longer then you have to, so perhaps call ahead.

I would not go there alone.  Unless you are physically intimidating on the outside.  I feel uneasy being in there, but I'm 5'6" and asian.

Food will probably give you a heart attack, but it hits the spot.

Food is ok here. I recently moved to the Allegheny area of North Philly, which is rundown and in need of gentrification. The outside of this Chinese Take Away is very noticeable with its bright colors. The order area is encased in bulletproof glass because of the sketchy area. I ordered Happy Family and Wonton Soup; both of which were flavorful and not greasy. The only downside that I see to this place is the lack of acceptance of credit cards. There are atms inside, but with all the sketchy people around, I wouldn't risky using the atm inside. Arrive with cash ready!

reviews.text: A terrific little neighborhood pub. Everyone one should live near a spot like this. The food is excellent as is the beer selection. Friendly crowd and a great quizzo spot too. Its not fine dining or the beer emporium but it is a nice place to catch a game or hook up with friends.

Pete's is like my home away from home. This is the first place my partner and I ate at when viewing our would-be apartment and I'm pretty convinced it's the reason we signed the lease! After 2 years of devoted patron-ism, it's time I write a proper review. The food here is awesome, the beer is always nice, and the guys behind the bar make a great cocktail.
Menu favorites: 
-Hummus, always served with three different types from goats cheese to scallion to pepper      
and plenty enough flatbread for dipping. 
-Nachos are tasty, massive, and totally enough for 2, even 3. 
-The daily soups are always on point. 
- Steak salad is FANTASTIC. 
-I would skip over the turkey burger and opt for the beef burger which is super tasty. 
-The chicken salad sandwich is a definite win and the house salad served with is so fresh with a house made ( I think white balsamic vinegar) dressing. 
-We've only ordered off the brunch menu once but the chicken and waffles stick out in my memory as being a great order. 
What I love about Pete's is that the staff sticks around. For as long as we've been going I haven't seen much change over, if any. They're great at their job and they seem to enjoy it. I've for sure been turned off by quite a few bars in Philly lately that seem to only hire the "hipster" (I hate using that word, but it just fits) type that can barely make time to take your order because they're entertaining friends at the end of the bar. Pete's is the total opposite; welcoming, friendly, and just the right amount of attentive. 
Also, Pete's is very linked in with Old Swede's Church across the road, and frequently team up for gigs and benefits. That little corner of Queen's Village really does feel like one big family. 
A side note: parking around Pete's is generally actually super easy. I'm hesitant to give away the secret, seeing as we frequent those spaces, but parking in front of the church on the cobblestone or under 95 is the way to go. 
See you there!

The only r reason this is not five stars is because every time I come here, the service is slower than those DSL turtles.

Expect to wait, but if you're sitting outside with your friends, enjoying a Hoegardden in the sun, waiting is just fine. 

The food is pretty damn good. You can't go wrong munching on the hand-cut fries. And at lunch I recommend the "Chicken Salad Sandwich:
Grilled Chicken, Diced Apricots & Red Onion on Raisin Walnut Bread
Served w/ a House Salad, $7"

name: Popeyes Louisiana Kitchen
description: Fast Food, American (Traditional), Food, Chicken Shop, Chicken Wings, Desserts, Restaurants

reviews.text:
This Popeye's Chicken shack sits in a long commercial strip on Trenton Road, Morrisville, Pa.  It is a standard franchise for the company.  The space is clean and attractive, with a well hidden drive thru component around to the back.  

I went in the other evening for a light dinner and to help nourish my life long Southern Fried Chicken addiction. I just can't seem to get enough.  Love the crunch and the hot oil burning my fingers. Love the spicy coat.  Love the way it pulls away from the bone with a little coaxing. 

These days, fried chicken is offered on the more sophisticated menus, and even for breakfast with waffles for those who just want max carb load.  (I'm not there yet.)  But, just because someone with a chef's hat and culinary school degree puts a batch together doesn't mean it is any better than the cheaper, faster, mass produced variety.  In fact, there is a school of thought that fried chicken is like singing the blues.  You know; "You have to suffer if you want to sing the blues..." Those hands playing six string acoustic or even Lucille, bring something to the experience that can be felt deep in the soul.  

Chicken be that way, too.  The true fried chicken artists, like the best Delta or Hills Blues guitarists and singers, are rooted in a culture and existential angst that generates the creative instinct leading to emotionally charged performances.  Those same forces are at work with fried chicken.  In the hands of a master, the chicken becomes an extension of his life, the same way a great song emerges from that primordial place deep in the heart.

This 2 piece box o' chicken may not have been epic, but it was solid and even inspired this review.  So, even though we weren't sitting in Muscle Shoals, Alabama in a roadside chicken house, there was enough there to let the imagination run wild.

Just wish they actually played that music at Popeye's, rather than the current soundtrack.

My only complaint about this store and most other Popeyes in the surrounding area is that they never have tenders fresh. They always make you wait at least  5 minutes for fresh ones. I guess it better than getting nasty dry chicken lol. I make sure that I never get food from here unless I have the time to wait.

My better half was craving southern-style chicken tenders and biscuits. Reviews for this Popeyes location were good so took a detour on the way home to pick up the food order.

Prior reviews mentioned that this was a clean location and this is very apparent when one steps into this joint. The interiors are super clean and well maintained (including the rest rooms). 

The chicken tenders were freshly prepared and the last time we had memorably good ones from a fast food spot was at a service area at 5AM (was the first batch). The side of blackened ranch was zesty and paired well with the crispy and spicy tenders. Hit the sweet spot for us and left us feeling so satisfied. Would definitely come back here in the future. Very friendly customer service.

reviews.text:
the service was great.
i had a few sushi rolls. they were all tasty and fresh.
i had some kind of tea. i dont know what it was but it was delicious. some kind of white grape tea concoction.

dessert was on the house which was a friendly gesture. some kind of banana thing. it was also flavorful. 
everything was served quickly and with a smile! plus it's BYOB so thats earns its own star in my book.

LOVE this place. My fiancé and I live down the street from here and go about once a week. The salmon nigiri is my FAVORITE. I actually wasn't a huge plain fish person when I started eating here, I liked crunchy/spicy specialty rolls more, but the quality of Hikari's fish is so good that I've converted! And yes, to the point of other reviewers, it is expensive, but the food is actually worth it. The service is also excellent. The woman who is our usual waitress, Ina, is incredibly sweet and attentive. It's a chill place to go with friends or even solo with a book and some wine  Highly recommend this spot!!

Have finally got around to going here and loved it, look forward to going back again soon and especially look forward to sitting outside on a nice evening drinking saki and devouring large amounts of sushi! Byob so be sure to stop an get a nice big bottle of something!
